FBIS3-22094 "jptdd013__l94097" JPRS-tdd-94-013-L Document Type:JPRS Document Title:Narcotics 21 March 1994 WEST EUROPE ITALY Further on Heroin Seizure in Trieste AU2103193294 Vienna ORF Television Network in German 1830 GMT 21 Mar 94 AU2103193294 Vienna ORF Television Network Language: German Article Type:BFN [Text] In Trieste, 300 kg of heroin have been seized. This is the largest amount of heroin ever seized by Italian authorities. The heroin was found in an Austrian truck [as received]. The driver has been arrested. The forwarding agent, based in [the Austrian province of] Styria, has also been taken to prison. The heroin was found in the truck that had been on a ferry crossing from Turkey. The official load was fruit and spice. The 80 percent pure heroin was to be sold in the Dutch, German, Italian, and Austrian markets. The smugglers had used pepper and paprika to divert the sniffer dogs' attention.
